      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>Cocaine has been prepared by a sequence beginning with a Mannich reaction (Problem 23-45) between dimethyl acetonedicarboxylate, an amine, and a dialdehyde. Show the structures of the amine and dialdehyde.</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBc2dZIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--26549ed7aa71f2c4899787e60582345aedd39411/OChem_23_EC_033.jpg\" alt=\"The reaction shows dimethyl acetonedicarboxylate with an amine and dialdehyde, forming a cyclic seven-membered carbonyl compound with a bridged N-methyl group. The structure of cocaine is shown in parenthesis.\">",
